# Files that execute on Linux (WSL, CI, inside containers) must keep LF
# line endings even when checked out on Windows.  CRLF breaks:
#   - shell shebangs        (/usr/bin/env: 'bash\r': No such file or directory)
#   - Dockerfile line continuations (backslash followed by \r)
#   - patch application     (CRLF context lines never match LF source files)
*.sh            text eol=lf
Dockerfile*     text eol=lf
*.patch         text eol=lf
CMakeLists.txt  text eol=lf
